The paper deals with the problem of learning appropriate domain-specific bias, which is a core problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a method for learning many related tasks from the same domain, which is a common approach in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also provides a theoretical analysis of the method, which is a common practice in the field of machine learning. The paper's focus on learning bias and related tasks suggests that it is most likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE).
